Steam has updated its performance statistics for the most popular Internet service providers connecting to its platform. South Africans downloaded 564.8TB from Steam at an average rate of 7.8Mbps over the past week, stated Valve. This accounted for 0.2% of the total traffic downloaded from the platform during the period. The table below ranks the most popular ISPs in South Africa accessing Steam, based on the number of bytes delivered to that network from Steam. Steam does not detail the number of bytes delivered â€“ however, it does show the average download rates of the ISPs.